item.title: 行业竞争白热化，中国百度推出两款新人工智能模型
item.description: 中国百度周日表示，它已推出两款新的人工智能模型：多模态ERNIE 4.5和一款名为X1的新推理模型，力争在竞争激烈的人工智能竞赛中脱颖而出。【原文：China's Baidu said on Sunday it has launched two new artificial intelligence models, the multimodal ERNIE 4.5 and a new reasoning-focused model called X1, as it vies to stand out in a fiercely competitive AI race.】

item.title: 法新社报道：Telegram 的杜罗夫在调查中获准离开法国
item.description: 据法新社周六报道，法国当局已允许 Telegram 的俄罗斯籍创始人兼首席执行官帕维尔-杜罗夫（Pavel Durov）暂时离开法国，以减轻他在信息应用程序犯罪活动调查中的义务。【原文：French authorities have allowed Pavel Durov, the Russian-born founder and CEO of Telegram, to leave France temporarily in a loosening of his obligations under a probe into criminal activities on the messaging app, the French news agency AFP reported on Saturday.】

item.title: 印度 Zetwerk 公司联合创始人表示计划两年内上市
item.description: 印度 Zetwerk 公司首席执行官兼联合创始人周六表示，该公司正在考虑在 24 个月内上市，而此时这家合同制造商正在加紧电子产品的生产。【原文：India's Zetwerk is considering a stock market listing within 24 months, at a time when the contract manufacturer is ramping up electronics production, its CEO and co-founder said on Saturday.】

item.title: 美国之音员工休假，特朗普盟友称该机构 "无法挽救
item.description: 发给员工的电子邮件告诉他们不要进入工作场所或访问内部系统。【原文：Emails to staff told them not to enter their work premises or access internal systems.】

item.title: 国媒称中国将打击股市假新闻，因为人工智能刺激了错误信息的传播
item.description: 据官方媒体周六报道，中国证券监察机构将加强对股市虚假信息的监控，并与警方和网络空间监管机构合作，打击那些因人工智能而变得更加容易的虚假新闻传播者。【原文：China's securities watchdog will step up monitoring fake information in the stock market and work with the police and cyberspace regulators to crack down on those who disseminate false news, which is being made easier by AI, official media reported on Saturday.】

item.title: 国媒称中国应选择 "适当时机和力度 "放松货币政策
item.description: 周六，中国国家媒体称，中国在放松货币政策时应选择合适的时机和力度，这是一个最新的信号，表明为提振世界第二大经济体而采取的进一步宽松政策可能不会迫在眉睫。【原文：China should choose the right timing and force in easing monetary policy, state media said on Saturday in the latest signal that further easing to boost the world's second-largest economy may not be imminent.】

item.title: 埃隆-马斯克：搭载特斯拉机器人的星际飞船将于 2026 年底飞往火星
item.description: SpaceX 公司创始人埃隆-马斯克（Elon Musk）周五表示，"星际飞船 "将于明年年底搭载特斯拉仿人机器人 "擎天柱 "前往火星。【原文：SpaceX founder Elon Musk said on Friday that Starship is set to depart for Mars at the end of next year, carrying Tesla humanoid bot Optimus.】

item.title: OpenAI 和马斯克同意就营利性转变进行快速审判
item.description: OpenAI 和埃隆-马斯克（Elon Musk）已同意加快对 OpenAI 营利性转变的审判，这是世界首富与 OpenAI 首席执行官山姆-奥特曼（Sam Altman）之间的恩怨情仇在法庭上公开上演的最新一幕。【原文：OpenAI and Elon Musk have agreed to fast-track a trial over OpenAI's for-profit shift, the latest turn in a grudge match between the world's richest person and OpenAI CEO Sam Altman playing out publicly in court.】

item.title: 埃隆-马斯克的 SpaceX 要求美国解决外国贸易壁垒问题
item.description: 美国太空探索技术公司（SpaceX）敦促美国解决影响其在外国提供 Starlink 卫星通信服务的贸易壁垒问题，认为来自国外的竞争对手在美国没有进口成本。【原文：SpaceX has urged the U.S. to address trade barriers affecting its Starlink satellite communications service in foreign countries, arguing that competitors from abroad face no import costs in the country.】

item.title: 伯克希尔哈撒韦公司董事奥尔森下台，巴菲特反对股东提案
item.description: 伯克希尔-哈撒韦公司（Berkshire Hathaway）周五表示，长期董事罗纳德-奥尔森（Ronald Olson）将离开董事会，因为政策变化要求除沃伦-巴菲特（Warren Buffett）外，其他董事在年满 80 岁后必须卸任。【原文：Berkshire Hathaway said on Friday longtime Director Ronald Olson will be leaving its board because of a policy change requiring directors, except for Warren Buffett, to step down after turning 80.】

item.title: 制药商同意参加第二轮价格谈判
item.description: 联邦卫生机构周五表示，包括诺和诺德（Novo Nordisk）和梯瓦制药公司（Teva Pharmaceuticals）在内的所有药品生产商都已同意参与第二轮价格谈判。【原文：All drug manufacturers, including Novo Nordisk and Teva Pharmaceuticals , whose medicines are part of the second round of price talks have agreed to participate in the negotiation process, a federal health agency said on Friday.】

item.title: 资产管理公司 VanEck 申购 Avalanche ETF，因另类币热潮升温
item.description: VanEck周五申请了一只交易所交易基金，该基金将跟踪Avalanche公司的avax币的价格，资产管理公司正寻求利用人们对比特币以外的加密货币日益增长的兴趣。【原文：VanEck filed for an exchange-traded fund on Friday that will track the price of Avalanche's avax coin, as asset managers seek to capitalize on the growing interest in cryptocurrencies beyond bitcoin.】

item.title: 韩国贸易部要求美国豁免关税
item.description: 韩国贸易部周六表示，韩国贸易部长已要求美国贸易部长在美国对韩国征收的互惠关税于四月生效时免除韩国的关税。【原文：South Korea's trade minister has asked his U.S. counterpart to exempt the country from reciprocal tariffs if they go into effect in April, the trade ministry said on Saturday.】

item.title: 科尔百货更改 DEI 官员头衔，扩大供应商多元化计划
item.description: 科尔百货公司（Kohl's）周五更改了其首席供应商多元化倡议官的头衔，并扩大了其供应商多元化计划，以回应唐纳德-特朗普总统在联邦政府和私营部门推动废除这一做法的呼声。【原文：Kohl's on Friday changed the title of its chief DEI officer and broadened its supplier diversity program in response to President Donald Trump's push to dismantle the practice in the federal government and private sector.】

item.title: 通用电气航空航天公司获得 18 亿美元的美国空军合同
item.description: 通用电气航空航天公司周五表示，已从美国空军获得一份价值高达 18 亿美元的合同。【原文：GE Aerospace said on Friday it had secured a contract from the U.S. Air Force valued up to $1.8 billion.】

item.title: 英特尔新任首席执行官基本工资为 100 万美元
item.description: 美国芯片制造商英特尔公司在周五提交的一份监管文件中表示，该公司新任首席执行官陈立武将获得100万美元的初始基本工资。【原文：U.S. chipmaker Intel's new CEO Lip-Bu Tan will receive an initial base salary of $1 million, the company said in a regulatory filing on Friday.】

item.title: 大型航空公司质疑拜登航空收费规则的裁决
item.description: 美国上诉法院今年 1 月做出裁决，认定交通部有权制定航空公司费用披露规则，各大航空公司周五对这一裁决提出质疑。【原文：Major air carriers on Friday challenged a U.S. appeals court ruling in January that found the Transportation Department has authority to write airline fee disclosure rules.】

item.title: 交易日：动荡的一周以周五的繁荣结束
item.description: 交易日【原文：TRADING DAY】

item.title: 瑞典金融科技公司 Klarna 披露美国 IPO 文件
item.description: 瑞典支付公司 Klarna 周五公布了其在美国首次公开募股的文件，此前数月，该公司已秘密向监管机构提交了上市申请，备受瞩目。【原文：Swedish payments firm Klarna made public its paperwork for an initial public offering in the U.S. on Friday, months after confidentially filing with regulators for the much-anticipated listing.】

item.title: 美国副总统万斯告诉 NBC 新闻，他希望在 4 月 5 日前达成 "高水平 "的 TikTok 协议
item.description: 美国副总统 JD Vance 周五表示，他希望在 4 月 5 日最后期限之前达成 "高水平 "的 TikTok 协议。【原文：U.S. Vice President JD Vance said on Friday he expects a "high level" TikTok deal by the April 5 deadline.】

item.title: 独家报道：墨西哥大亨斯利姆看中墨西哥石油公司的两个重要油田，在能源领域的影响力日益增强
item.description: 熟悉内情的消息人士告诉路透社，墨西哥国家能源公司 Pemex 正在与卡洛斯-斯利姆（Carlos Slim）进行谈判，这位亿万富翁可能会为该国最有前途的两个原油和天然气田提供资金支持。【原文：Mexican state energy company Pemex is in talks with Carlos Slim which could see the billionaire tycoon help bankroll two of the country's most promising crude oil and natural gas fields, sources familiar with the matter told Reuters.】

item.title: (官方）CERAWEEK 高管称人工智能将带来更快、更便宜的石油生产
item.description: 在休斯顿举行的 CERAWeek 会议上，高管们详细介绍了人工智能正在加快石油和天然气钻探的速度，并促使公司重新审视那些他们认为开发难度过大或成本过高的地方。【原文：Artificial intelligence is speeding up oil and gas drilling and prompting companies to take a second look at places they had viewed as too difficult or expensive to develop, executives detailed during the CERAWeek conference in Houston.】

item.title: 聚焦：特朗普引发的动荡吸引新投资者投资黄金
item.description: 为躲避美国新政府引发的政治和经济动荡，越来越多的投资者开始转向黄金交易所交易基金，为市场创纪录的反弹增添了动力。【原文：Investors seeking shelter from political and economic volatility triggered by the new U.S. administration are increasingly moving into gold Exchange-Traded Funds, adding momentum to the market's record rally.】

item.title: 美国最高法院允许美国金融业监管局对阿尔派证券提起诉讼
item.description: 美国最高法院周五拒绝停止金融业监管局驱逐其成员之一--经纪自营商阿尔派证券--的程序，该案挑战了华尔街自我监管机构执法权的合宪性。【原文：The U.S. Supreme Court declined on Friday to halt a Financial Industry Regulatory Authority proceeding to expel one of its members, broker-dealer Alpine Securities, in a case challenging the constitutionality of the Wall Street's self-regulator's enforcement power.】
